│ THOUGHT: The root issue is the destructor asserting because reinserted instructions (without parent) skip       │
│ cleanup due to an early 'continue;'. They aren't processed by dropAllReferences or dead-user collection, so     │
│ they may still have users when erasing, triggering the assert. The minimal, semantics-preserving fix is to      │
│ remove that 'continue;' so reinserted instructions are also processed in the same loop, ensuring they get their │
│ references dropped and dead users collected before erasure. This keeps assertions and IR semantics intact.      │
│                                                                                                                 │
│ ```bash                                                                                                         │
│ awk '                                                                                                           │
│   BEGIN{inDtor=0}                                                                                               │
│   {                                                                                                             │
│     print                                                                                                       │
