│ THOUGHT: The destructor asserts because some live instructions get scheduled for deletion. The robust,          │
│ semantics-preserving fix is to:                                                                                 │
│ - Ensure we never add live (non-use-empty) instructions to DeletedInstructions (guard insertions for I and VI). │
│ - Restore the original destructor control flow by re-adding the early continue after temporary reinsertion, so  │
│ we don’t process those again in the same loop.                                                                  │
│ - Keep the safer dyn_cast_or_null in the destructor for operand scanning to avoid asserts on non-existent       │
│ values.                                                                                                         │
│ This preserves upstream behavior and avoids erasing live instructions. I will update the insertions and re-add  │
│ the continue, then submit the patch.                                                                            │
│                                                                                                                 │
│ ```bash                                                                                                         │
│ python3 - << 'PY' && submit-patch                                                                               │
│ import re, sys                                                                                                  │
│                                                                                                                 │
│ p = 'llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp'                                                           │
│ with open(p, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:                                                                       │
│     s = f.read()                                                                                                │
│                                                                                                                 │
│ # 1) Guard insertions into DeletedInstructions for I and VI (avoid scheduling live instructions).               │
│ # In eraseInstruction(I)                                                                                        │
│ s =                                                                                                             │
│ re.sub(r'(\beraseInstruction\s*\(\s*Instruction\s*\*I\s*\)\s*\{[^}]*?)\bDeletedInstructions\s*\.\s*insert\s*\(\ │
│ s*I\s*\)\s*;',                                                                                                  │
│            r'\1if (I->use_empty()) DeletedInstructions.insert(I);', s, flags=re.S)                              │
│ # In removeInstructionsAndOperands - first for-loop adding I from DeadVals                                      │
│ s =                                                                                                             │
│ re.sub(r'(\btemplate\s*<\s*typename\s*T\s*>\s*void\s*removeInstructionsAndOperands\([^}]*?for\s*\(\s*T\s*\*V\s* │
│ :\s*DeadVals\s*\)\s*\{\s*[^}]*?auto                                                                             │
│ \*I\s*=\s*cast<Instruction>\(V\);\s*)\bDeletedInstructions\s*\.\s*insert\s*\(\s*I\s*\)\s*;',                    │
