│ THOUGHT: The crash occurs because BoUpSLP::~BoUpSLP drops references for all scheduled instructions and then    │
│ asserts they have no users. If some instructions have external users (not in DeletedInstructions), the assert   │
│ fires. A safe, semantics-preserving fix is:                                                                     │
│ - Only drop references and erase instructions that have no external users (i.e., all their users are also in    │
│ DeletedInstructions).                                                                                           │
│ - Leave any instruction with external users untouched (no dropAllReferences, no erase), preventing IR breakage  │
│ and assertion failure.                                                                                          │
│ - Preserve the assertion by asserting only for the subset we’re erasing.                                        │
│ This avoids changing visible IR transformations and stabilizes teardown.                                        │
│                                                                                                                 │
│ ```bash                                                                                                         │
│ python3 - << 'PY' && submit-patch                                                                               │
│ import sys                                                                                                      │
│                                                                                                                 │
│ path = 'llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp'                                                        │
│ with open(path,'r',encoding='utf-8') as f:                                                                      │
│     src = f.read()                                                                                              │
│                                                                                                                 │
│ sig = 'BoUpSLP::~BoUpSLP()'                                                                                     │
